==Sutra mounds==
About 40 {{ill|Sutra mound|en|Sutra mound|qid=Q7650105|lt=Sutra mound|1=Sutra mound}}s have been confirmed at the summit of Mount Asakuma. The existence of the mounds was known since the {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji era|1=Meiji era}}, but more mounds were found after damage caused by the 1959 Isewan Typhoon. The mounds consist of a chamber built from mountain stones, and many were found to contain artifacts from end of the Heian period. In 1966, the area was designated as a National Historic Site, and many of the excavated items were collectively designated as a National Treasure in 1963. Many of these items are exhibited in the temple museum.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://kunishitei.bunka.go.jp/heritage/detail/201/863 |title=Database of Registered National Cultural Properties |publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] |accessdate=10 April 2011}}</ref> These include bronze sutra containers, mirrors with [[Amitābha|Amida]] and the Amida triad, and ceramics.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sips03.narahaku.go.jp/exhib/2007toku/shinbutsu/shinbutsu-2_01_e.htm |title=Exhibition - list of entries (No.50) |publisher=[[Nara National Museum]] |accessdate=10 April 2011 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719232853/http://sips03.narahaku.go.jp/exhib/2007toku/shinbutsu/shinbutsu-2_01_e.htm |archivedate=19 July 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bunka.pref.mie.lg.jp/bunkazai/da/item/detail.asp?pub=1&pub=2&speclass=1&spetype=1&spetype=2&spetype=3&dettype=9&wag=7&prePageNum=1&mngnum=0000483 |title=Artifacts from the Kyōgamine sutra mound |publisher={{ill|Mie Prefecture|en|Mie Prefecture|qid=Q128196|lt=Mie Prefecture|1=Mie Prefecture}} |accessdate=10 April 2011 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110911113647/http://www.bunka.pref.mie.lg.jp/bunkazai/da/item/detail.asp?pub=1&pub=2&speclass=1&spetype=1&spetype=2&spetype=3&dettype=9&wag=7&prePageNum=1&mngnum=0000483 |archivedate=11 September 2011 }}</ref> The area of funerary monuments where these items were found has been designated an {{ill|List of Special Places of Scenic Beauty, Special Historic Sites and Special Natural Monuments|en|List of Special Places of Scenic Beauty, Special Historic Sites and Special Natural Monuments|qid=Q20982902|lt=Historic Site|1=List of Special Places of Scenic Beauty, Special Historic Sites and Special Natural Monuments}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://kunishitei.bunka.go.jp/heritage/detail/401/1525 |title=Database of Registered National Cultural Properties |publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] |accessdate=10 April 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bunka.pref.mie.lg.jp/bunkazai/da/item/detail.asp?pub=1&pub=2&speclass=4&spetype=11&wag=7&prePageNum=1&mngnum=0000489 |title=Mount Asama Kyōzukagun |publisher={{ill|Mie Prefecture|en|Mie Prefecture|qid=Q128196|lt=Mie Prefecture|1=Mie Prefecture}} |accessdate=10 April 2011 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110911113729/http://www.bunka.pref.mie.lg.jp/bunkazai/da/item/detail.asp?pub=1&pub=2&speclass=4&spetype=11&wag=7&prePageNum=1&mngnum=0000489 |archivedate=11 September 2011 }}</ref>

==Buildings==
The '''Hondō''' is a seven by six {{ill|Ken (unit)|en|Ken (unit)|qid=Q3195007|lt=bay|1=Ken (unit)}}, ''[[:en:Yosemune-zukuri|Yosemune-zukuri]]'' building with a ''[[hinoki]]'' bark roof. Built in 1609, it is an {{ill|Important Cultural Property (Japan)|en|Important Cultural Property (Japan)|qid=Q1188622|lt=Important Cultural Property|1=Important Cultural Property (Japan)}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://kunishitei.bunka.go.jp/heritage/detail/102/1295 |title=Database of Registered National Cultural Properties |publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] |accessdate=10 April 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bunka.pref.mie.lg.jp/bunkazai/da/item/detail.asp?pub=1&pub=2&speclass=1&spetype=1&spetype=2&spetype=3&dettype=1&wag=7&prePageNum=1&mngnum=0000453 |title=Kongōshō-ji Hondō |publisher={{ill|Mie Prefecture|en|Mie Prefecture|qid=Q128196|lt=Mie Prefecture|1=Mie Prefecture}} |accessdate=10 April 2011 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110911113234/http://www.bunka.pref.mie.lg.jp/bunkazai/da/item/detail.asp?pub=1&pub=2&speclass=1&spetype=1&spetype=2&spetype=3&dettype=1&wag=7&prePageNum=1&mngnum=0000453 |archivedate=11 September 2011 }}</ref>

